00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:56.860
I have g over lambda cubed, and
then this f plus evaluated at z

00:19:56.860 --> 00:20:02.860
equals to 1, which is
this zeta function of 5/2.

00:20:02.860 --> 00:20:03.470
OK?

00:20:03.470 --> 00:20:05.210
So fine.

00:20:05.210 --> 00:20:08.490
So what do I have for energy?

00:20:08.490 --> 00:20:15.260
Energy is going to be at
3/2 V times this formula,

00:20:15.260 --> 00:20:21.870
kd T g over lambda
cubed zeta 5/2.

00:20:21.870 --> 00:20:30.590
And I noticed that lambda, being
h square root of 2 pi mk T,

00:20:30.590 --> 00:20:33.950
scales like T to the minus 1/2.

00:20:33.950 --> 00:20:37.870
So 1 over lambda cubed
scales like T to the 3/2 plus

00:20:37.870 --> 00:20:40.890
this is something that's
scaling like T to the 5/2.

00:20:45.120 --> 00:20:49.030
And this is simply proportional
to the volume and temperature

00:20:49.030 --> 00:20:50.780
to the [INAUDIBLE] fifth power.

00:20:50.780 --> 00:20:54.460
It knows nothing
about the density.

00:20:54.460 --> 00:20:55.010
Why?

00:20:55.010 --> 00:20:59.650
Because if you were at the
same temperature and volume,

00:20:59.650 --> 00:21:02.020
put more particle
in the system, all

00:21:02.020 --> 00:21:04.630
of those additional
particles would go over here,

00:21:04.630 --> 00:21:10.370
would make no contribution
to pressure or to energy.

00:21:10.370 --> 00:21:12.420
You wouldn't see them.

00:21:12.420 --> 00:21:16.450
So once you have this, the heat
capacity at constant volume,

00:21:16.450 --> 00:21:24.860
dE by dT, is simply 5 over
2T of whatever energy is.

00:21:35.960 --> 00:21:41.300
And there is a reason that
I write it in this fashion.

00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:43.810
So what you would
say is that if I

00:21:43.810 --> 00:21:50.030
were to plot the heat
capacity at constant volume

00:21:50.030 --> 00:21:56.040
as a function of
temperature, well,

00:21:56.040 --> 00:22:01.646
