at this point.

00:28:54.290 --> 00:29:00.440
And actually, in order to
show that, all we need to do

00:29:00.440 --> 00:29:06.540
is to figure out what these
terms do when I evaluate them

00:29:06.540 --> 00:29:09.660
at z equals to 1.

00:29:09.660 --> 00:29:12.690
And because these
things are telling

00:29:12.690 --> 00:29:16.105
me what is happening as I am
approaching to this point,

00:29:16.105 --> 00:29:19.360
the question that I ask is,
what is the limiting behavior

00:29:19.360 --> 00:29:23.800
of this function as I
get to z equals to 1?

00:29:23.800 --> 00:29:26.070
But the limiting value
of this one I know.

00:29:26.070 --> 00:29:28.340
It is precisely what
