00:29:41.580 --> 00:29:44.110
How can I get that?

00:29:44.110 --> 00:29:47.170
Well, all of these things
are done under the conditions

00:29:47.170 --> 00:29:50.040
where the volume is fixed,
or the number of particles

00:29:50.040 --> 00:29:52.390
is fixed, if the
density is fixed.

00:29:52.390 --> 00:29:58.090
So z and T are related
through the formula that

00:29:58.090 --> 00:30:03.450
says N over V, which
is the density,

00:30:03.450 --> 00:30:09.260
is g over lambda
cubed f 3/2 plus of z.

00:30:09.260 --> 00:30:10.520
OK?

00:30:10.520 --> 00:30:14.450
So if I take the system and
I change its temperature,

00:30:14.450 --> 00:30:17.540
while keeping the number
of particles, volume,

00:30:17.540 --> 00:30:20.300
fixed so that the
density is fixed,

00:30:20.300 --> 00:30:25.270
if I take d by dT on both
sides, on the other side

00:30:25.270 --> 00:30:29.550
I'm assuming that I'm doing the
calculations under conditions

00:30:29.550 --> 00:30:31.970
where the density
does not change.

00:30:31.970 --> 00:30:34.740
And then what do
I have over here?

00:30:34.740 --> 00:30:38.030
I have to take the temperature
derivative of this.

00:30:38.030 --> 00:30:40.180
There's an implicit
derivative here

00:30:40.180 --> 00:30:44.280
since this is T to the
3/2 proportionately.

00:30:44.280 --> 00:30:52.150
So when I take a derivative,
I will get 3 over 2T,

00:30:52.150 --> 00:30:59.030
and then I will have
f 3/2 plus of z.

00:30:59.030 --> 00:31:03.550
But then I have to take
the derivative that

00:31:03.550 --> 00:31:06.565
is implicit in the
dependence on z here.

00:31:06.565 --> 00:31:14.250
And that's going to
be identical to this,

00:31:14.250 --> 00:31:17.960
except that when I take
a derivative of f 3/2,

00:31:17.960 --> 00:31:23.660
I will generate f 1/2 of z.

00:31:23.660 --> 00:31:25.030
OK?

00:31:25.030 --> 00:31:29.690
So since the left-hand
side is equal to 0,

00:31:29.690 --> 00:31:31.850
I can immediately
solve for this,

00:31:31.850 --> 00:31:39.590
and I find that T
dz by dT 1 over z

00:31:39.590 --> 00:31:51.920
is minus 3/2 f 3/2 plus of z
divided by f 1/2 plus of z.

00:31:51.920 --> 00:31:54.360
OK?

00:31:54.360 --> 00:32:02.370
So essentially, what I can do
is I can multiply through by T.

00:32:02.370 --> 00:32:07.740
So this T will get rid of this
T. I can bring a T, therefore,

00:32:07.740 --> 00:32:09.320
here.

00:32:09.320 --> 00:32:12.930
And this combination
over here I can

00:32:12.930 --> 00:32:21.510
replace from what I have there
with minus 3/2 f 3/2 plus of z

00:32:21.510 --> 00:32:24.226
divided by f 1/2 half plus of z.

00:32:27.960 --> 00:32:30.990
Why is any of this useful?

00:32:30.990 --> 00:32:35.340
Well, it immediately gives
the answer that I need.

00:32:35.340 --> 00:32:37.130
Why?

00:32:37.130 --> 00:32:44.290
Because f 1/2 is the
derivative of this function.

00:32:44.290 --> 00:32:46.590
And you can see that
I drew it so that it

00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:50.620
has infinite derivative
when z hits 1.

00:32:50.620 --> 00:32:55.930
And we had indeed said that
this function zeta of m, which

00:32:55.930 --> 00:32:59.640
is the limit of this
when z goes to 1,

00:32:59.640 --> 00:33:03.160
only exists for m
that is larger than 1,

00:33:03.160 --> 00:33:07.840
and it is divergent for
m that is less than 1.

00:33:07.840 --> 00:33:15.590
So when z hits 1, this
thing goes to infinity,

00:33:15.590 --> 00:33:18.720
and the fraction disappears.

00:33:18.720 --> 00:33:22.490
And so basically, the
additional correction

00:33:22.490 --> 00:33:26.680
that you have beyond this
becoming zeta of 5/2,

00:33:26.680 --> 00:33:30.290
which is what we have
over here, vanishes.

00:33:30.290 --> 00:33:35.870
So I have shown that, indeed,
whatever this curve is doing,

00:33:35.870 --> 00:33:43.080
it will hit that point
exactly at Tc of n

00:33:43.080 --> 00:33:46.830
at the same height as the
low temperature curve.

00:33:46.830 --> 00:33:51.090
And you can do a certain
amount of work and algebra

00:33:51.090 --> 00:33:56.450
to show that it goes
there with a finite slope.

00:33:56.450 --> 00:33:59.020
So that's the shape
of the heat capacity

00:33:59.020 --> 00:34:02.317
curve for the
Bose-Einstein condensate.

